news.title: ITC Hotels' profit up 74% at ₹133 crore in Q2 FY26
news.para: ITC Hotels announced a significant 74 percent increase in its second-quarter net profit. This growth was driven by higher revenues from operations.  The company's revenue from operations increased to Rs 839.48 crore.

news.title: Schindler expects China's construction slump to persist through 2026
news.para: As the construction crisis in China looks set to persist, Schindler predicts a challenging road for lift and escalator orders through 2026. Yet, the company remains optimistic, having raised its annual margin forecast thanks to tighter operational efficiency, thoughtful pricing strategies, and a refined product mix.

news.title: Indian real estate records 42 transactions valued at $2.9 billion in July-Sept quarter
news.para: The July-September quarter was a landmark period for India's real estate industry, marking the highest level of institutional investment ever recorded. Investors flocked from various sectors, engaging in a total of 42 transactions that collectively reached $2.9 billion.

news.title: World Bank likely to release another $200 million for Amaravati capital project by December 2025
news.para: The World Bank is set to release another USD 200 million for Amaravati Capital Phase-I development by year-end. This follows an initial disbursement of USD 207 million. The World Bank and ADB are jointly funding USD 1600 million for the project. Regular inspections by the World Bank and ADB teams are ongoing.

news.title: Andhra Pradesh government rolls out unified zoning policy for urban areas
news.para: Andhra Pradesh has unified its zoning policy across all urban bodies to streamline development and end confusion from varied land use rules. Previously, 16 separate categories caused complexity. This move, inspired by other states, aims for standardized land use, simplifying building permissions and promoting sustainable growth in cities and towns.

news.title: Regularising building under Karnataka's e-Swathu scheme? Pay tax from 2016
news.para: Owners regularising unauthorised properties in Karnataka under the e-Swathu scheme will now pay property tax retrospectively. This tax will be calculated from either 2016 or the year an electricity connection was obtained. Panchayats will assess and recover these dues promptly. New rules also fix fees for NOCs and building plan approvals, with collections managed by gram panchayats.

news.title: Booming commercialisation drives residents out of Jubilee Hills, Hyderabad
news.para: Rapid commercialisation between 2000 and 2014 prompted affluent Jubilee Hills residents to sell homes and relocate, shifting voter registrations to other constituencies. Once a symbol of aspiration, the prestigious neighbourhood now grapples with land scams and corruption, despite its allure for celebrities and leaders.

news.title: Secunderabad: SH-1 property tax hike on hold amid protests
news.para: Secunderabad Cantonment Board has paused a 100% property tax hike for owners along SH-1 until a road widening issue is resolved. Property owners facing income loss will receive a 50% discount, offering much-needed relief amidst tenant departures due to the project.

news.title: Haryana: Online deed registration must from November 1
news.para: Haryana is set to become one of India's first states to achieve 100% paperless deed registration by November 1, 2025. This digital transformation will streamline property transactions, offering citizens a transparent and user-friendly platform for registration and verification. The phased rollout ensures a smooth transition to the new system across all 22 districts.

news.title: How 'negligence' gutted offices in Mumbai high-rise
news.para: A massive fire engulfed a 13-storey Jogeshwari building, suspected to have flouted safety norms and lacked an Occupation Certificate.  Despite no casualties, 27 were treated for suffocation.  Tenants allege illegal alterations and a non-functional fire system, leading to significant losses for businesses.

news.title: Telangana HC flags surge in illegal constructions, warns lawyers & builders
news.para: The Telangana High Court has issued a stern warning to lawyers against taking up cases involving illegal constructions, citing a grave threat to the state's future. Justice B Vijaysen Reddy emphasized accountability for current authorities and urged vigilance from municipal officials and builders.

news.title: Chennai: ₹2,000 crore housing scam alleged inside Pallikaranai Ramsar site
news.para: An NGO has accused government departments of illegal approvals for a housing project. The project is allegedly inside the Pallikaranai Ramsar wetland. Arappor Iyakkam claims environmental and construction clearances were wrongly granted. The NGO submitted evidence showing the project site is within the wetland boundaries. This raises serious questions about the approval process.

news.title: Nagpur: Officials inspect Laxmi Nagar fire site, structural audit likely
news.para: Following a massive fire at a commercial-residential building in Laxmi Nagar, Nagpur Municipal Corporation officials are investigating potential unauthorized constructions and fire safety violations. A structural audit is underway to assess the building's stability before reoccupation.

news.title: CBRE raises full-year profit forecast on strong leasing demand
news.para: CBRE, a leading real estate firm, has revised its profit expectations upward for the year, buoyed by a strong demand for leasing and facilities management services. The company's stock experienced a boost during early trading hours.

news.title: Protest for Oran land registration in Jaisalmer ends
news.para: A 34-day protest for Oran-Gochar land recognition concluded successfully. Negotiations with the Jaisalmer district administration led to an agreement. The administration will register nearly one lakh bighas of land, including specific Oran lands, within three months. Surveys of traditional water sources and heritage sites will also be conducted. This marks a historic move for the region.

news.title: Mindspace REIT to add 7-8 million sq ft over next four years
news.para: Mindspace REIT in an interview with ETRealty in September informed about robust 94% occupancy and a 20% re-leasing spread, driven by strong demand from Global Capability Centers and domestic firms. The company is expanding its portfolio organically and through acquisitions, with plans for 7-8 million sq ft under construction.

news.title: Nexus Select Trust to double mall portfolio by FY30; plans ₹5,000-6,000 crore capex via debt-equity mix
news.para: Nexus Select Trust REIT plans to significantly expand its retail portfolio to 18-20 million sq ft across 30-35 malls by FY30. The REIT will fund its ₹5,000-6,000 crore capital needs through debt and equity, leveraging strong portfolio metrics like 98% occupancy and consistent rental growth.

news.title: Odisha RERA to appoint land expert to streamline dispute resolution
news.para: Odisha Real Estate Regulatory Authority is appointing a land expert to help resolve complex property disputes. This move follows the introduction of a new standard operating procedure (SOP) for registering part plots across the state. The new guidelines aim to simplify registrations for family settlements, land transfers, and urban expansions.

news.title: TTDC takes possession of its land housing private hotel in Trichy
news.para: Tamil Nadu Tourism Development Corporation (TTDC) has taken possession of a private star hotel in Trichy for non-payment of lease dues. The hotel, leased on TTDC land since 1994, owed ₹38 crore upon lease expiry. Despite legal challenges, the hotel failed to pay the directed ₹20 crore, leading to the takeover.
